", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/21499", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21499", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21499.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21499.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>This pull request addresses issues encountered when trying to build tensorflow with cuda support on debian based systems (stretch and buster)</p>\n<p>The current tensorflow build process does not work with the debian maintained cuda packages. This is because there are some differences in the paths where the libraries are installed.</p>\n<p>Summary of changes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Update to configure.py to search <code>&lt;cuda_root&gt;/lib/x86_64-gnu-linux</code>  for libcudart in addition to <code>&lt;cuda_root&gt;/lib64</code></li>\n<li>Update to bazel configure script to find cupti header and library</li>\n<li>Update to bazel configure script to find NVVM device files</li>\n</ul>", "body_text": "This pull request addresses issues encountered when trying to build tensorflow with cuda support on debian based systems (stretch and buster)\nThe current tensorflow build process does not work with the debian maintained cuda packages. This is because there are some differences in the paths where the libraries are installed.\nSummary of changes:\n\nUpdate to configure.py to search <cuda_root>/lib/x86_64-gnu-linux  for libcudart in addition to <cuda_root>/lib64\nUpdate to bazel configure script to find cupti header and library\nUpdate to bazel configure script to find NVVM device files", "body": "This pull request addresses issues encountered when trying to build tensorflow with cuda support on debian based systems (stretch and buster)\r\n\r\nThe current tensorflow build process does not work with the debian maintained cuda packages. This is because there are some differences in the paths where the libraries are installed.\r\n\r\nSummary of changes:\r\n- Update to configure.py to search `<cuda_root>/lib/x86_64-gnu-linux`  for libcudart in addition to `<cuda_root>/lib64`\r\n- Update to bazel configure script to find cupti header and library\r\n- Update to bazel configure script to find NVVM device files"}